entities.name: ElizaOS
entities.description: A modular containerized program system for building and deploying AI agents, featuring a cloud MVP, credit system, and API key management. It aims to provide a platform for developers to create and monetize AI applications through MCPs and workflow assembly.

entities.name: bun
entities.description: Fast JavaScript runtime, bundler, and package manager. Known for its performance optimizations in tasks like build processes.

entities.name: Comput3
entities.description: A company offering AI model subscriptions and access, integrating with various platforms and models. They provide tiered subscription levels for AI model access.

entities.name: Sonnet 4
entities.description: A subscription tier offered by Comput3 for AI model access, available on 8xB200s via Kimi K2.

entities.name: Kimi K2
entities.description: An AI model provided by Comput3, accessible through Sonnet 4 subscriptions and currently offered with free access.

entities.name: Qwen Coder 480B
entities.description: An AI model offered by Comput3, with free access provided at launch by logging in with Solana.

entities.name: Solana
entities.description: A decentralized blockchain network known for its speed and scalability. It is used for authentication and accessing services on Comput3.

entities.name: REVOX
entities.description: A platform collaborating with ElizaOS to provide human-like avatars with personality and emotion for AI agents through their DEVA platform.

entities.name: DEVA
entities.description: The platform developed by REVOX that enables AI agents to have human-like avatars with personality and emotion.

entities.name: tsup
entities.description: A project that provides a build system optimization tool, which was replaced by bun.Build in ElizaOS to improve build times.

entities.name: ChatGPT
entities.description: A large language model developed by OpenAI. It serves as a default provider in certain ElizaOS functions when other handlers are not properly triggered.

entities.name: WSL
entities.description: Windows Subsystem for Linux, an environment that allows running Linux distributions on Windows. Users reported permission errors when creating agents within WSL.

entities.name: ERC-8004
entities.description: A standard designed to add a trust layer for agent interactions across organizations, focusing on identity, reputation, and task validation.

entities.name: CNBC of prediction markets
entities.description: A conceptual show that combines prediction markets with content creation, aiming to provide market news and analysis in a format akin to CNBC.

entities.name: Reneil
entities.description: A user who announced Comput3's upcoming Sonnet 4 level subscriptions.

entities.name: Kenk
entities.description: A user who shared a comprehensive summary of agents presented at the accelerator demo day and provided explanations of the ERC-8004 standard.

entities.name: Odilitime
entities.description: A user who recommended the browserbase plugin for ElizaOS and commented on the maintenance status of the built-in plugin-browser.

entities.name: Shaw
entities.description: A user who developed the browserbase plugin for ElizaOS, recommended for browser automation despite its cost.

entities.name: Eliza.how
entities.description: A website resource for individuals looking to build and utilize the ElizaOS platform.

entities.name: docs.eliza.ai
entities.description: The official documentation website for ElizaOS, providing resources for developers and users.

entities.name: Fleek.xyz
entities.description: A website that facilitates the launching of agents using the Eliza platform.

entities.name: n8n
entities.description: A workflow assembly system that ElizaOS plans to emulate for chaining Modular Containerized Programs (MCPs) together.

entities.name: Quantum
entities.description: A project that powers the 'Pump This Page' feature, which includes quantitative and executional agents, a new Web Extension, and a tokenization feature.

entities.name: EIP-8004
entities.description: An Ethereum Improvement Proposal that aims to add a trust layer for agent interactions across organizations, focusing on identity, reputation, and task validation. It is being discussed for potential integration with ElizaOS.

entities.name: Collab.land
entities.description: A platform used for identity verification and community management, with potential issues leading to discussions of switching to Vulcan.xyz.

entities.name: Vulcan.xyz
entities.description: A platform being considered as a potential replacement for Collab.land due to verification issues experienced with the latter.

entities.name: OpenRouter
entities.description: A service that provides an API gateway for accessing multiple LLM providers. They experienced a temporary issue with their Generations API endpoint.

entities.name: Cloudflare
entities.description: A web infrastructure and security company that provides services like CDNs and DNS. Issues with Cloudflare indirectly affected OpenRouter's Generations API endpoint.

entities.name: daos.fun
entities.description: A platform associated with the $ai16z token, with a design that reportedly causes issues with the token's functionality. ElizaOS team is working on a plan to address this.

entities.name: Motzl
entities.description: A user who confirmed that the $ai16z token is the main token of the project.

entities.name: CJFT
entities.description: A user who led a significant refactoring effort in ElizaOS, replacing tsup with bun.Build to optimize build times.

entities.name: sam-developer
entities.description: A user who reported improvements to Eliza cloud infrastructure, including stable text generation support and analytics dashboard refinements.

entities.name: Bond11
entities.description: A user who mentioned building 'Hivemind,' an AI-powered crypto marketing strategist showcased at the ElizaOS Accelerator Demo Day.

entities.name: elizalabs.ai
entities.description: A domain associated with ElizaOS that was identified as lacking SPF setup, posing a potential security vulnerability for email spoofing.

entities.name: Jin
entities.description: A user who is working on prediction markets combined with content creation and has been considering the idea of a 'CNBC of prediction markets' show.

entities.name: Dean
entities.description: A user who identified Fleek.xyz as the website for launching agents using Eliza.

entities.name: $ai16z
entities.description: The main token of the ElizaOS project, which has experienced reported issues related to its functionality on the daos.fun platform.

entities.name: browserbase plugin
entities.description: A plugin recommended for browser automation with ElizaOS, developed by Shaw, known for its effectiveness despite its cost.

entities.name: plugin-browser
entities.description: A built-in plugin within ElizaOS for browser automation that has not been maintained and is considered basic in its functionality.
